weather.description: This game is going to be absolutely frigid, temps in the teens (16 degrees or so at kickoff and falling), plus a 10mph wind that will put the wind-chill value somewhere right around 0-5 degrees. To make matters worse (better?), it's going to snow. A Winter Storm Warning has been issues, and total snowfall before and during the game should be somewhere around 2-3 inches. This is truly fantastically bad weather, and I only wish the winds were a little whippier to give it a true "fade". With winds being manageable I think there's still some viable path to scoring here, I once watched Brady throw for 5TD's in one quarter (not an exaggeration) in the snow, remember that snow makes it tough on the defense too.
Scattered light showers possible, especially pre-game and early game.
